{{Redirect|Body swapping|the Red Dwarf episode|Bodyswap}} {{Essay-like|article|date=December 2008}} A '''body swap''' is a [[Literary technique|storytelling device]] seen in a variety of science and supernatural fiction, in which two people (or beings) exchange minds and end up in each other's bodies. In media such as television and film, the device is an opportunity for two actors to temporarily play each other's characters,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.us/tv/20677/6-staples-of-sci-fi-and-fantasy-television|title=6 staples of sci-fi and fantasy television|author=|date=|website=denofgeek.us|accessdate=7 May 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315042020/http://www.denofgeek.us/tv/20677/6-staples-of-sci-fi-and-fantasy-television|archivedate=15 March 2016|df=}}</ref> although in some cases, dialogue is [[dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbed]] by the original actors.
There are different types of body swapping. For non-technology swapping, switches can be caused by [[magic item]]s such as amulets, heartfelt [[wish]]es, or just strange quirks of the [[universe]]. The switches typically reverse after the subjects have expanded their [[world view]]s, gained a new appreciation for each other's troubles by literally "walking in another's shoes" and/or caused sufficient amounts of [[farce]]. Notable examples include the books ''[[Vice Versa (book)|Vice Versa]]'' (1882)<!-- No, that's STILL NOT a typo --> and<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allreaders.com/Topics/Info_17775.asp|title=Vice Versa by F. Anstey Detailed Book Review|last=Jose|first=Michael JR|accessdate=24 November 2010|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110408092030/http://www.allreaders.com/Topics/Info_17775.asp|archivedate=8 April 2011|df=}}</ref> ''[[Freaky Friday]]'' (1972),<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sptimes.com/News/020401/Hernando/The_mother_versus_the.shtml|title=The mother versus the author|last=King|first=Robert|date=February 4, 2001|work=St. Petersburg Times|accessdate=24 November 2010|location=Hernando|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110523033908/http://www.sptimes.com/News/020401/Hernando/The_mother_versus_the.shtml|archivedate=23 May 2011|df=}}</ref> as well as the film versions of both.
Switches accomplished by technology, exempting gadgets [[Clarke's three laws|advanced sufficiently]] to appear as magic, are the fare of [[mad scientist]]s. Body-swapping devices are usually characterized by a highly experimental status, straps, helmets with many complicated cables that run to a central system and a tendency to direly malfunction before their effects can be reversed. Those without such means may resort to [[whole-body transplant|brain transplant]]s. Such experiments can have overtones of [[Horror fiction|horror]].{{Citation needed|date=February 2010}}
==Appearances in fiction and drama== {{main|Body swap appearances in media}}
<!--- please list body swaps where it is a key aspect of the media. minor episodes should be put in the list above. ---> Since the ''[[Vice Versa (novel)|Vice Versa]]'' novel was published in 1882, body swaps have been a popular theme in various media: * ''[[Boy Meets Girl (miniseries)|Boy Meets Girl]]'' (2009 TV miniseries) — Two strangers swap bodies when struck by lightning. *''[[The Change-Up]]'' (2011 film) – A lawyer and family man switches with his best friend who is an adult video actor.<ref name="vulture">{{cite web |last=Raymond |first=Adam K. |url=http://www.vulture.com/2011/08/how_to_swap_bodies_with_anyone.html |title=How to Swap Bodies With Anyone You Want, According to the Movies |work=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture.com]] |date=2013-09-05 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004212915/http://www.vulture.com/2011/08/how_to_swap_bodies_with_anyone.html |archivedate=2013-10-04 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ebert |first=Roger |authorlink=Roger Ebert |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-change-up-2011 |title=The Change-Up Movie Review & Film Summary (2011) |work=RogerEbert.com |date=2011-08-03 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004221449/http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-change-up-2011 |archivedate=2013-10-04 |df= }}</ref> * ''[[Dating the Enemy]]'' (1996 film) — An Australian comedy about a boyfriend and girlfriend who swap bodies and have to live as each other. * ''[[Freaky Friday]]'' (1972 book) — Mother and daughter. Disney produced a film in 1976 and remakes in 1995 and 2003. Several television shows have used ''Freaky Friday'' or variants of for their episode titles. This also inspired the ''Freaky Freakend'' sitcom block where several TV shows on [[Disney Channel]] featured body swapping episodes. *''[[The Hot Chick]]'' (2002 film) – A popular high school cheerleader finds herself in a man's body.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ebert |first=Roger |authorlink=Roger Ebert |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-hot-chick-2002 |title=The Hot Chick Movie Review & Film Summary (2002) |work=RogerEbert.com |date=2002-12-13 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005010414/http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-hot-chick-2002 |archivedate=2013-10-05 |df= }}</ref> *''[[The Identity Matrix]]'' (1982 novel by [[Jack L. Chalker]]) – Victor Gonser swaps with various women as part of an alien body swapping scheme.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_w3kPAAACAAJ |title=The Identity Matrix – Chalker – Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-02}}</ref> *''[[It's a Boy Girl Thing]]'' (2006 film) – Male teen and neighbor girl.<ref name="vulture"/> *''[[Laughing Gas (novel)|Laughing Gas]]'' (1936 novel by [[P. G. Wodehouse]]) – Reggie and Joey inhale laughing gas at a dentist's office and find they have swapped bodies. * ''[[Prelude to a Kiss (play)|Prelude to a Kiss]]'' (1988 play) – A mysterious old man kisses a bride on her wedding day and switches bodies. It was [[Prelude to a Kiss (film)|adapted into a 1992 film]] that starred [[Alec Baldwin]] and [[Meg Ryan]].<ref name="vulture"/> *'' [[Secret Garden (South Korean TV series)|Secret Garden]]'' (South Korean drama) &ndash; A stuntwoman switches bodies with a handsome CEO. *''[[The Thing on the Doorstep]]'' (1937 short story by [[H. P. Lovecraft]]) *''[[Yamada-kun and the Seven Witches]]'' (2012 manga by [[Miki Yoshikawa]]) – A boy and a girl are able to switch bodies with a kiss.<ref name="yoshikawa_interview">{{cite web |url=http://mahouxscans.wordpress.com/2013/02/03/yoshikawa-interview/ |title=Yoshikawa Interview &#124; Mahou-X |publisher=Mahouxscans.wordpress.com |date=2013-02-03 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213931/http://mahouxscans.wordpress.com/2013/02/03/yoshikawa-interview/ |archivedate=2013-10-04 |df= }} – translation of ''[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]'' article.</ref><ref name="yoshikawa_interview2">{{cite web |url=http://natalie.mu/comic/pp/yamadakuntomajo |title=コミックナタリー – [Power Push&#93; 「山田くんと7人の魔女」吉河美希インタビュー (1/4) |publisher=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie.mu]] |language=Japanese |date=2013-02-03 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215123/http://natalie.mu/comic/pp/yamadakuntomajo |archivedate=2013-10-04 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-01-06/crunchyroll-adds-inside-mari-silver-nina-love-theory-manga |title=Crunchyroll Adds Inside Mari, Silver Nina, Love Theory Manga – News |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2014-01-06 |accessdate=2014-01-08 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108091410/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-01-06/crunchyroll-adds-inside-mari-silver-nina-love-theory-manga |archivedate=2014-01-08 |df= }}</ref> *''[[Your Name]]'' (2016 anime film by [[Makoto Shinkai]]) – A teenage boy and girl intermittently swap bodies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/your-name-makoto-shinkai-anime-body-swap/|title='Your Name' Director Makoto Shinkai on Updating the Body-Swap Movie|author=|date=6 December 2016|website=thewrap.com|accessdate=7 May 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180507130720/https://www.thewrap.com/your-name-makoto-shinkai-anime-body-swap/|archivedate=7 May 2018|df=}}</ref>
